Function Reference/maybe redirect 404 « WordPress Codex
-----------

Applies only for WordPress Multisite installation

Correct 404 redirects when NOBLOGREDIRECT is defined

Usage
-----

` <?php maybe_redirect_404() ?> `

Parameters
----------

This function does not accept any parameters

Return Value
------------

This function does not return any value. If all conditions are met, it
does not return at all, rather the redirect is executed.

Examples
--------

Notes
-----

If registration is disabled, please set NOBLOGREDIRECT in wp-config.php
to a URL you will redirect visitors to if they visit a non-existent
site:

    define( 'NOBLOGREDIRECT', '%siteurl%' );

or

    define( 'NOBLOGREDIRECT', 'http://www.my-ms.com' );

Change Log
----------

Since: [MU](/Version_MU "Version MU")

Source File
-----------

`maybe_redirect_404()` is located in `wp-includes/ms-functions.php`

